import HelloApp.*;
import org.omg.CORBA.*;
import java.util.Properties;

public class Client {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            // Setup ORB properties before initialization
            Properties props = new Properties();
            props.put("org.omg.CORBA.ORBInitialPort", "1050");
            // Optionally specify host if needed:
            props.put("org.omg.CORBA.ORBInitialHost", "localhost");  //Here "localhost" is needed
            // Initialize ORB once with properties
            ORB orb = ORB.init(args, props);

            // Using corbaloc (no naming service)
            org.omg.CORBA.Object obj = orb.string_to_object("corbaloc:iiop:localhost:1050/Hello");
            
	        //ncRef.rebind(ncRef.to_name("Hello"), href);
	        Hello helloRef = HelloHelper.narrow(obj);

            String response = helloRef.sayHello();
            System.out.println("Server says: " + response);

        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}


Code Explanation
================
List the methods of ORB?

In CORBA, the ORB (Object Request Broker) is the core component that enables communication between clients and distributed objects. It provides several methods for initialization, object reference handling, and request processing.

Here’s a clear list of the commonly used ORB methods, grouped for easier understanding:

1. ORB Initialization
	Used to start the ORB:

	init()
	✅init(String[] args, Properties props)

	Initializes the ORB instance.

2. Initial References
	Used to obtain references to core CORBA services:

	resolve_initial_references(String name)
	list_initial_services()

	Example: "RootPOA", "NameService"

3. Object String Conversion
	Convert object references to/from strings:
	object_to_string(org.omg.CORBA.Object obj)
	✅string_to_object(String str)

	Useful for storing/transferring object references.

4. Dynamic Invocation Support
	create_list(int count)
	create_named_value(String name, Any value, int flags)
	create_exception_list()
	create_context_list()
	get_default_context()

5. Any Type Handling
	Methods to work with CORBA’s universal container type (Any):
	create_any()

6. TypeCode Creation
	Used for describing data types dynamically:
		get_primitive_tc(TCKind kind)
		create_struct_tc(...)
		create_union_tc(...)
		create_enum_tc(...)
		create_alias_tc(...)
		create_exception_tc(...)
		create_interface_tc(...)
		create_string_tc(int bound)
		create_sequence_tc(int bound, TypeCode element_type)
		create_array_tc(int length, TypeCode element_type)

7. Request Processing
	Control ORB event loop:
		run()
		shutdown(boolean wait_for_completion)
		work_pending()
		perform_work()

8. Policy & Environment
		get_service_information(short service_type, ServiceInformationHolder info)
		create_policy(int type, Any val)
 
Key Idea
========
The ORB is responsible for:
	Initializing CORBA environment
	Locating objects
	Converting object references
	Handling requests and communication

